title: Catch-22: See TCU's final scoring play from a 55-52 shootout win over Texas Tech
text:
College football teams needs a little luck every now and then. TCU happened to have a little of it at just the right time.
On a fourth and goal play, TCU quarterback Trevone Boykin tried to throw a pass to Josh Doctson (who already had 18 catches up to this point of the game). And then this happened.
You just never know... #TCU pic.twitter.com/E5KFwViaMM
â” Rachel Nichols (@Rachel__Nichols) September 27, 2015 You can also hear TCU's radio call of the touchdown by clicking here.
TCU's college football playoff hopes are still alive to Aaron Green's heads up play.
